# gen56 (C2b) / gen63 (C2c): a social marker must not hijack a turn that also
# carries real content. These are MIXED acts; the substance is routed to a
# content module. marker-only turns are still handled by the dialogue-act layer.
> hello
< Hi there!
> hi, what can you do?
< I can answer questions about facts and rules, do simple arithmetic, reason about cause and effect, compare quantities, tell whether two things are the same, remember things you tell me, read a short passage and pull out facts, track what a pronoun refers to, continue a sequence you teach me, remember what we talked about.
> hey, who are you?
< I am parrot0.
> hello. what exactly are you?
< I am parrot0.
> hi, my dog is called Rex.
< Got it: your dog is called Rex.
> thanks, that was wrong
< I don't understand that yet.

